The paper deals with the application of randomized dimension reduction schemes to the context of persistent homology, which involves the study of topological features of data sets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
